                    <div>
                        <head>State of preservation</head>
                        <p>The surface is even, but heavily worn. Large chunks have flaked off. The first 6 columns are not legible, except for four characters at the end of column 6. A horizontal crack, running through segments 1D to 7D, has been widening since the 1980s. Another crack, 113 cm above the floor, begins about 40 cm from the rear wall e and continues for about 80 cm. It is followed in segments 6B and 6C by an area, 99–117 cm above the ground and ca. 18 cm wide, where the surface has completely fallen off. The wall’s deterioration has already been discussed in detail in the Introduction. </p><!--<p>Another crack, 113 cm above the floor, begins ca. 40 cm from wall e and continues for ca. 80 cm. It is followed for another 45 cm by a flaked off area, 99–117 cm above the ground, and ca. 18 cm wide. Here many more characters are destroyed. The rubbings taken in the 1980s still show many characters clearly that have since disappeared, for example in segments 5-A, 5-B, 6-B. Part of the engraved layer flaked off after September 2010 and was found lying on the ground/floor on October 6, 2012.</p>-->
                        <figure rend="left" n="figure" xml:id="map_cave_76_EN.svg">
                            <head xml:lang="zh">
                                <hi rend="bold">76</hi>號窟平面圖。雷魯卡根據馬本漢和王平國田野繪圖製作</head>
                            <head>Ground plan of cave <hi rend="bold">76</hi>; drawing by Lukas Ledderose after field map by MB and MS</head>
                            <graphic url="map_cave_76_EN.svg"/>
                        </figure>
